【transforms/Dataset/DataLoaderの役割】¶

transforms¶

　・データ前処理を定義するモジュール¶

Dataset¶

　・データと対応するラベルを1組返すモジュール¶
　・transformsを使って定義した前処理を画像データに対して行うモジュール¶

DataLoader¶

　・データセットからデータをバッチサイズに固めて返すモジュール¶


transformsDatasetDataLoader DataLoader

# transforms
data_transforms = {
    'train': transforms.Compose([
        transforms.Resize(256),
        transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5), # p=0.5
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), # [0.485, 0.456, 0.406][0.229, 0.224, 0.225]
    ]),
    'val': transforms.Compose([
        transforms.Resize(256),
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]),
    ]),
}

# device, target_num
device = "cpu"
target_num = 2

# 
def get_model(target_num):
    model_ft = models.resnet18(pretrained=True)
    model_ft.fc = nn.Linear(512, target_num)
    model_ft = model_ft.to(device)
    return model_ft

# ResNet18
pretrained_model = get_model(target_num=2)

# 
print(pretrained_model)

      (conv1): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1), bias=False)
      (bn1): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      (conv2): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False)
      (bn2): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (downsample): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2), bias=False)
        (1): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      )
    )

    )
  )

  (fc): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=2, bias=True)

# loss,acc
train_loss_tensor = []
train_acc_tensor = []
val_loss_tensor= []
val_acc_tensor = []


# 
def train_model(model, criterion, optimizer, num_epochs, is_saved=False):
    best_acc = 0.0
    
    # 
    for epoch in range(num_epochs):
        
        print('', epoch+1)
        
        for phase in ['train', 'val']:
            print('{}:'.format(phase))

            # 
            if phase == 'train':
                model.train() 
            else:
                model.eval()  

            running_loss = 0.0
            running_corrects = 0
  
            # dataloaders(=5)1540
            for i, (inputs, labels) in enumerate(image_dataloaders[phase]):
                inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)

                # 1. optimizer
                optimizer.zero_grad()
                    
                # 2.(5)inputoutput
                outputs = model(inputs)
                _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)

                # 3. outputloss
                loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
                
                # 5loss
                if (i+1) % 5 == 0:
                    print('   loaders:{}'.format(i+1)  ,'   loss:{}'.format(loss))
                    
                # loss
                if phase == 'train':
                    train_loss_tensor.append(loss)
                else:
                    val_loss_tensor.append(loss)

                # 
                if phase == 'train':                        
                    # 4. 
                    loss.backward()
                    # 5. optimizer
                    optimizer.step()

                # loss = loss  5
                running_loss += loss.item() * inputs.size(0)
                #  = 
                running_corrects += torch.sum(preds == labels.data)

            # lossloss
            epoch_loss = running_loss / dataset_sizes[phase]
            # Accuracy
            epoch_acc = running_corrects.double() / dataset_sizes[phase]
            print('{} Loss: {:.4f} {} Acc: {:.4f}'.format(phase, epoch_loss, phase, epoch_acc))
            
            # acc
            if phase == 'train':
                train_acc_tensor.append(epoch_acc)
            else:
                val_acc_tensor.append(epoch_acc)

            # C. 
            if phase == 'val' and epoch_acc > best_acc:
                best_acc = epoch_acc
                if(is_saved):
                    torch.save(model.state_dict(), './original_model.pth')
                    
    print('Best val Acc: {:4f}'.format(best_acc))
